msContents.summary: Copy of al-Qūshjī's short work on astronomy with some diagrams in red.

supportDesc.extent: 66 foliated leaves : 220 x 150 (165 x 100) mm, bound to 230 x 160 mm

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in nastaʻlīq in black ink; pointed.

decoNote: Chapter headings and diagrams in red ink.

binding.p: Quarter covers with light blue paper sides over card.

origin.p: Copy completed in 1206 AH by Rājah Rāī Harbans Singh (f. 66v).

provenance: Formerly owned by David Eugene Smith (bookplate inside front cover).
